        <abstract> 
<p>Responds to JDD’s letter [<hi rend="doubleUnderline">3845</hi>].</p> 
            <p>Discusses his own poor health.</p>
            <p>"Man is our great subject at present."</p> 
<p>Lyell’s book [<hi rend="italic">Antiquity of man</hi> (1863)] sold 4000 copies on day of sale.</p>  
<p>"The fossil bird [<hi rend="italic">Archaeopteryx</hi>] … is a grand case for me." Wishes a skeleton could be found in the "so-called red sandstone foot-step beds".</p> 
        </abstract>
